snippet.textDisplay:
BEST IKEA STORY TIME
How my friend and his entire family got banned from their local Ikea 🏡❤️

My friends father in law was visiting from out of town. He stayed at their house instead of at a hotel to spend time with the grandkids (I’m assuming) He was currently battling digestive issues and had to take laxatives to make everything flow. This is important for later 😁

Fast forward to my friend taking his wife and kids to Ikea for an innocent family shopping trip while grandpa stayed home to rest. 👩🏻‍🤝‍👨🏼👱🏻‍♀️👦🏻👶🏼My friend sends his children to the play area while he and his wife divide and conquer. He told them to stay there until he came to pick them up, charging his oldest daughter to make sure her brothers stayed put. Now, imagine his surprise when he later turns around to see his youngest son holding one of Ikea’s strategically placed teddy bears 👶🏼🐻 Concerned, my friend asks his son why he would leave the play area and wander alone. His son stretched the stuffed plush towards his fathers face saying he wanted to show him the new toy he found. Of course 😑 SUDDENLY, my friend then notices something odd about the teddy bear. 🤔

The fur is a little mussed and there seems to be an odd smell lingering? He looks a little closer, his son still beaming at his accomplishment, and notices that the bear is COVERED in poop. Then he notices HIS SON is covered in poop! Horrified, he glances behind his son to see a TRAIL of poop behind him. Poop is sliding down one of his son’s legs and forming a little pile on the floor. He snatches up his son and runs through ikea, following the poop trail. It takes him back to the play area where every bit of play equipment has his sons diarrhea on it. Toys, slides, stuffed animals, you name it- - pooped. Turns out when they got home the kid had gotten into grandpas ‘chocolates’ (laxatives) and had him a couple handfuls.

Long story short they had to evacuate the play area and disinfect everything the kid touched and got banned from Ikea 🤗
